name: Freestyle Session 8 Double DVD
description:
Freestyle Session 8 just found a bunch of these in my storage so made them available again.  Very limited quantities get these before they are gone for good!  

Freestyle Session 8 Day 2 FSS8 2 Disc Collectors Edition DVD

Promoter: Cros One

Format: NTSC Region 1 DVD - Universal

Rating: Not Rated

On August 22, 2004, 62 of the world's best crews competed for over $20,000.00 in cash & prizes and the right to represent the United States at the Freestyle Session World Finals in Japan.

Over 4,000 spectators boarded the historic Queen Mary ship to find out who was the best of the best in the largest crew battle ever to take place in B-Boy history. Witness battling at its best. This is Freestyle Session VIII-

"That's one show I wanted to be at the most! Anyone into the true forms of this culture was either there or pissed they couldn't make it!" -DJ QBert, Thud Rumble

"Cros1 gets major props for not letting the system beat him down. He's given B-Boys & B-Girls platforms around the world through his event for all of us to treat as one of our playgrounds. Don't let this event stop. It's needed!" -Crazy Legs, Rock Steady Crew

Disc 1: Feature

- Previews

- Intro by Jivan Ivan of Breakvision

- Shutting down Aquadome

- Full event B-Boy Battles

- The best crews from the U.S., Finland, Canada, and Japan

- Before & Afters

- Sick & tired of watching battles one after the other? We left the camera rolling for you to see & hear more-

- Sneak peeks on the next Freestyle Sessions

- Freestyle Session VIII Day 2 Trailer

- Feature Run Time: Approx. 180 minutes

Disc 2: Extras

- Behind-the-scenes

- The full story on the controversy that moved the event to the Queen Mary ship

- Uncut ciphers

- Aside from battles, check out the drama that went down at Freestyle Session VIII

- Deleted scenes

- Trailers

name: Spin Beanies
description:
Spin Hats started by Armory/Freestyle Session's very own CROS1.  These are the original spin beanies since 1998.  Originally these style beanies were made by CROS1's mom for him to bust in.  Everytime he rocked them people would be like yo I want one I want one.  So slowly his mom made a few for some of his friends like Iron Monkey, and others.  Eventually before going to Pro Am 1998 his mom made 30 of them for him to sell.  At the event the beanies sold out in less then 15 minutes.  So after that he had his mom make them before all the events eventually the demand got so great that eventually the mass production duties went to his Aunt since she was a master at sewing.  And to this day he keeps the duties to his family instead of getting them made for cheaper overseas.  Its all about keeping it in the family!

*there are alot of fake and bootleg versions of this beanie out there.  Support the ORIGINAL!
